<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">this question can only be answered by yourself, considering the audience of your club. humboldt wrote about the abolition of slavery, the disastrous c<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">this question can only be answered by yourself, considering the audience of your club. humboldt wrote about the abolition of slavery, the disastrous consequences of reckless colonialism and the toil man is taking out on mother nature with his short-sightedness and wont for profit. he influenced people like darwin, goethe, jefferson, thoreau and muir, so his touch points spread over a plethora of fields. from religion, to literature and science, politics and being-human. in my opinion immense food for thought neatly woven around the life of a great person.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
